article.headline: UC Irvine 69, UC Davis 67
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. -- Darren Moore scored a game-high 21 points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead UC Irvine to a 69-67 win over UC Davis on Saturday night. The Anteaters (11-15, 4-8 Big West) snapped a four-game losing streak against the Aggies (10-14, 6-6), beating them for the first time since the 2007-08 season. Michael Hunter finished with 19 points for the Anteaters, which took a 29-22 scoring advantage in the second half to come back from a 40-45 deficit at the break. Todd Lowenthal and Dominic Calegari each scored 13 points for the Aggies, while Ryan Sypkens and Julian Welch each added 12.
